Our matter is currently in the hands of the Media Council of Kenya who will advise on the way forward. In the interim, the blackout on all FKF leagues and activities remains in full force.Meanwhile, I can’t wait for competitions that show respect for media to kick off... Like the annual Koth Biro Cup that lights up Ziwani every year.  Here, we don’t risk intimidation by FKF police!   Nick Mwendwa is very much like a bull in China shop. Or as the French say, an elephant in a porcelain store.
By forcing the StarTimes deal down the throats of all and sundry, the Football Kenya Federation (FKF) President is dealing a major dent on the corporate image of an otherwise well-meaning Chinese pay television concern.



