In essence, he is biting the hand that feeds him.
Events of last Saturday at the Nyayo National Stadium threw the spanner in the works.
In an attempt to contain Gor Mahia's dissent over the much-trumpeted StarTimes deal, FKF decided to lock out journalists who were deemed to be sympathetic to the record 18-times Kenyan league champions' cause, and “who would have live-streamed and documented K’Ogalo’s match in contravention of the StarTimes deal.”
Journalists who have worked tirelessly to enhance the Kenyan game, including colleagues from the Nation Media Group and Royal Media Services, were hounded out of the venue, like common criminals, by the police.



