The "crime" these journalists — who included senior Citizen TV Sports Editor Mike Okinyi, also the Secretary General of the Sports Journalists’ Association of Kenya — had committed was simply doing their professional job of showing up at the stadium to update audiences on the progress of a league they love so much.
Death knell being sounded
The last time I checked, newspapers don’t live-stream matches and it defeats us why our writers and photographers were locked out!
Granted, the other league matches countrywide went without incident, but if what happened at Nyayo on Saturday goes unmitigated, then the death knell is surely being sounded on corporate interest in Kenyan club football.



